## 8. Contexts

| Context | File | Purpose |
|---------|------|---------|
| `AuthContext` | AuthContext.tsx | Auth state, user, tokens, login/logout |
| `AccountsContext` | AccountsContext.tsx | Selected account, accounts list |
| `SidebarContext` | SidebarContext.tsx | Sidebar width, collapse state |
| `DateRangeContext` | DateRangeContext.tsx | Global date range filter |
| `GoogleSyncStatusContext` | GoogleSyncStatusContext.tsx | Google Ads sync status |
| `AssistantContext` | AssistantContext.tsx | AI assistant panel state |
| `GlobalStateContext` | GlobalStateContext.tsx | React Query provider, global state |

### Usage
```tsx
const { user, isAuthenticated } = useAuth();
const { selectedAccount } = useAccounts();
const { sidebarWidth } = useSidebar();
const { startDate, endDate } = useDateRange();
```

---

## 9. Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Examples |
|------|-----------|----------|
| Service file | camelCase | `accounts.ts`, `googleAdwordsCampaigns.ts` |
| Service object | camelCase + `Service` | `accountsService`, `googleAdwordsCampaignsService` |
| Query hook | `use` + Entity + Purpose | `useAccountsPaginated`, `useChannels` |
| Mutation hook | `use` + Action + Entity | `useCreateAccount`, `useUpdateAccount` |
| Query key | camelCase entity name | `queryKeys.accounts.all` |
| Context | PascalCase + `Context` | `AuthContext`, `AccountsContext` |
| Hook for context | `use` + Name | `useAuth()`, `useSidebar()` |

---

## 10. Checklist — New Service/Hook

1. [ ] Create service in `src/services/` following the module pattern
2. [ ] Define TypeScript interface for the entity
3. [ ] Add query keys in `src/hooks/queries/queryKeys.ts`
4. [ ] Create query hook in `src/hooks/queries/`
5. [ ] Create mutation hook in `src/hooks/mutations/` if needed
6. [ ] Invalidate relevant queries on mutation success
7. [ ] Handle 401/403 in retry logic
